# Threat Hunt: User Added to Administrators Group (Event ID 4732)

## Hunt Objective

Identify unauthorized privilege escalation through local group modifications.

---

## Threat Hypothesis

An attacker added an account to the Administrators group to gain elevated privileges.

---

## Data Source

- Windows Security Logs
- Microsoft Sentinel

---

## KQL Query

```kql
Event
| where EventID == 4732
| project TimeGenerated, Computer, RenderedDescription
```

---

## Investigation Steps

1. Identify the modified group.
2. Determine which account was added.
3. Identify who performed the action.
4. Verify approval for the change.
5. Review additional privilege escalation events.

---

## Expected Findings

- Administrator group changes
- Privileged account creation
- Unauthorized privilege escalation

---

## MITRE ATT&CK

| Tactic | Technique | ID |
|---------|-----------|----|
| Privilege Escalation | Account Manipulation | T1098 |

---

## Conclusion

Unexpected administrator group modifications are high-priority security events requiring immediate investigation.
